**That's 9 files and 25+ individual lines** for renaming just two columns. And this is your simplest table.

Renaming `profiles` columns is worse — `username`, `full_name`, `avatar_url`, `plan`, `is_public_profile`, and the social fields are scattered across [AuthContext.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/lib/AuthContext.jsx), [authService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/authService.js), [Profile.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/Profile.jsx), [PublicVault.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/PublicVault.jsx), [SharedVault.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/SharedVault.jsx), [CompleteProfile.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/CompleteProfile.jsx), and [plans.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/lib/plans.js).

### Adding a new table (e.g., `folders`)

| What you'd need to build | Exists today? |
|--------------------------|---------------|
| Service file for folder CRUD | ❌ No pattern for creating new service files quickly — each one is hand-written imperative code |
| React Query hooks for folder data | ❌ No custom hooks wrapping queries — each page writes its own inline `useQuery` |
| Relational join (prompts → folders) | ❌ No existing join queries to model from. Every query is flat single-table `.select('*')` |
| Migration strategy | ❌ No migration tooling. You'd manually alter tables in Supabase Dashboard |

### Difficulty: 🟠 Hard (for what should be easy)

Not because the change itself is complex, but because **there is no data mapping layer**. You're essentially hand-editing raw SQL column names scattered across your entire UI.

### Architecture failure point

```
Database Column Names → Service Functions → React Components → JSX Rendering
        ↑                                                          ↑
     ┌──┴──────── No transformation layer ─────────────────────────┘
     │
     └── Change here? Manually grep-and-replace across 9+ files.
```

### What would make this survivable

A **data transformation layer** — a simple function that maps database rows to app-level objects:

```js
// lib/mappers.js
export const mapPrompt = (row) => ({
  id: row.id,
  title: row.name,        // DB column → app field
  content: row.body,       // DB column → app field
  tags: row.tags || [],
  isPublic: row.is_public,
  usageCount: row.usage_count,
  createdBy: row.created_by,
  createdAt: row.created_at,
});
```

Change the DB column? Update one line in the mapper. UI code never sees raw column names.

